## Description {#details}

This file contains some templates that are useful if you are working with the STL at all.

No library is required when using these functions.

<Link id="l00590" /><CodeLine lineNumber="590"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The iterator isn&#39;t quite an &#96;OutputIterator&#96; or an &#96;InputIterator&#96; but</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00591" /><CodeLine lineNumber="591"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// somewhere between them. The constraints of these iterators are:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00592" /><CodeLine lineNumber="592"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00593" /><CodeLine lineNumber="593"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// - On construction or after being incremented, it is comparable and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00594" /><CodeLine lineNumber="594"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   dereferencable. It is &#42;not&#42; incrementable.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00595" /><CodeLine lineNumber="595"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// - After being dereferenced, it is neither comparable nor dereferencable, it</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00596" /><CodeLine lineNumber="596"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   is only incrementable.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00597" /><CodeLine lineNumber="597"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00598" /><CodeLine lineNumber="598"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// This means you can only dereference the iterator once, and you can only</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00599" /><CodeLine lineNumber="599"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// increment it once between dereferences.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00600" /><CodeLine lineNumber="600"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">template</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &lt;</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">typename</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> WrappedIteratorT&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00601" /><CodeLine lineNumber="601" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/early-inc-iterator-impl"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">class </span><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/early-inc-iterator-impl/#a5162b8e5b84a0d2cb14a3ddda8fca208">early&#95;inc&#95;iterator&#95;impl</a></span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00602" /><CodeLine lineNumber="602"><span class="doxyHighlight">    : </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">public</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/iterator-adaptor-base/#a8170d24cedaf5c2a22d8fc0c986529aa">iterator&#95;adaptor&#95;base</a>&lt;early&#95;inc&#95;iterator&#95;impl&lt;WrappedIteratorT&gt;,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00603" /><CodeLine lineNumber="603"><span class="doxyHighlight">                                   WrappedIteratorT, std::input&#95;iterator&#95;tag&gt; &#123;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00643" /><CodeLine lineNumber="643"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Make a range that does early increment to allow mutation of the underlying</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00644" /><CodeLine lineNumber="644"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// range without disrupting iteration.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00645" /><CodeLine lineNumber="645"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00646" /><CodeLine lineNumber="646"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The underlying iterator will be incremented immediately after it is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00647" /><CodeLine lineNumber="647"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// dereferenced, allowing deletion of the current node or insertion of nodes to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00648" /><CodeLine lineNumber="648"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// not disrupt iteration provided they do not invalidate the &#42;next&#42; iterator --</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00649" /><CodeLine lineNumber="649"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// the current iterator can be invalidated.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00650" /><CodeLine lineNumber="650"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00860" /><CodeLine lineNumber="860"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// zip iterator that assumes that all iteratees have the same length.</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01244" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1244"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The class represents the base of a range of indexed&#95;accessor&#95;iterators. It</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01245" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1245"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// provides support for many different range functionalities, e.g.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01246" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1246"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// drop&#95;front/slice/etc.. Derived range classes must implement the following</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01247" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1247"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// static methods:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01248" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1248"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   &#42; ReferenceT dereference&#95;iterator(const BaseT &amp;base, ptrdiff&#95;t index)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01249" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1249"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     - Dereference an iterator pointing to the base object at the given</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01250" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1250"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///       index.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01251" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1251"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   &#42; BaseT offset&#95;base(const BaseT &amp;base, ptrdiff&#95;t index)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01252" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1252"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     - Return a new base that is offset from the provide base by &#39;index&#39;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01253" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1253"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///       elements.</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01518" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1518"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Returns an opaquely-typed Callable object whose operator() overload set is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01519" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1519"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// the sum of the operator() overload sets of each CallableT in CallableTs.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01520" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1520"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01521" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1521"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The type of the returned object derives from each CallableT in CallableTs.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01522" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1522"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The returned object is constructed by invoking the appropriate copy or move</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01523" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1523"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// constructor of each CallableT, as selected by overload resolution on the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01524" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1524"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// corresponding argument to makeVisitor.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01525" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1525"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01526" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1526"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Example:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01527" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1527"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01528" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1528"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\code</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01529" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1529"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// auto visitor = makeVisitor(&#91;&#93;(auto) &#123; return &quot;unhandled type&quot;; &#125;,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01530" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1530"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///                            &#91;&#93;(int i) &#123; return &quot;int&quot;; &#125;,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01531" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1531"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///                            &#91;&#93;(std::string s) &#123; return &quot;str&quot;; &#125;);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01532" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1532"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// auto a = visitor(42);    // &#96;a&#96; is now &quot;int&quot;.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01533" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1533"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// auto b = visitor(&quot;foo&quot;); // &#96;b&#96; is now &quot;str&quot;.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01534" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1534"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// auto c = visitor(3.14f); // &#96;c&#96; is now &quot;unhandled type&quot;.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01535" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1535"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\endcode</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01536" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1536"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01537" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1537"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Example of making a visitor with a lambda which captures a move-only type:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01538" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1538"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01539" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1539"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\code</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01540" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1540"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// std::unique&#95;ptr&lt;FooHandler&gt; FH = /&#42; ... &#42;/;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01541" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1541"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// auto visitor = makeVisitor(</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01542" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1542"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     &#91;FH&#123;std::move(FH)&#125;&#93;(Foo F) &#123; return FH-&gt;handle(F); &#125;,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01543" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1543"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     &#91;&#93;(int i) &#123; return i; &#125;,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01544" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1544"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     &#91;&#93;(std::string s) &#123; return atoi(s); &#125;);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01545" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1545"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\endcode</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01609" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1609"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// array&#95;pod&#95;sort - This sorts an array with the specified start and end</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01610" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1610"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// extent.  This is just like std::sort, except that it calls qsort instead of</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01611" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1611"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// using an inlined template.  qsort is slightly slower than std::sort, but</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01612" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1612"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// most sorts are not performance critical in LLVM and std::sort has to be</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01616" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1616"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01617" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1617"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// This function assumes that you have simple POD-like types that can be</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01618" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1618"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// compared with std::less and can be moved with memcpy.  If this isn&#39;t true,</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01620" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1620"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02257" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2257"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Zippy iterator that uses the second iterator for comparisons. For the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02258" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2258"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// increment to be safe, the second range has to be the shortest.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02259" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2259"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Returns &#96;enumerator&#95;result&#96; on dereference to provide &#96;.index()&#96; and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02260" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2260"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// &#96;.value()&#96; member functions.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02261" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2261"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Note: Because the dereference operator returns &#96;enumerator&#95;result&#96; as a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02262" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2262"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// value instead of a reference and does not strictly conform to the C++17&#39;s</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02263" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2263"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// definition of forward iterator. However, it satisfies all the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02264" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2264"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// forward&#95;iterator requirements that the &#96;zip&#95;common&#96; and &#96;zippy&#96; depend on</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02265" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2265"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// and fully conforms to the C++20 definition of forward iterator.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02266" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2266"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// This is similar to &#96;std::vector&lt;bool&gt;::iterator&#96; that returns bit reference</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02411" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2411"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Given two or more input ranges, returns a new range whose values are</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02412" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2412"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// tuples (A, B, C, ...), such that A is the 0-based index of the item in the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02413" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2413"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// sequence, and B, C, ..., are the values from the original input ranges. All</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02414" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2414"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// input ranges are required to have equal lengths. Note that the returned</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02415" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2415"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// iterator allows for the values (B, C, ...) to be modified.  Example:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02416" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2416"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02417" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2417"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// &#96;&#96;&#96;c++</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02418" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2418"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// std::vector&lt;char&gt; Letters = &#123;&#39;A&#39;, &#39;B&#39;, &#39;C&#39;, &#39;D&#39;&#125;;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02419" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2419"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// std::vector&lt;int&gt; Vals = &#123;10, 11, 12, 13&#125;;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02420" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2420"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02421" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2421"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// for (auto &#91;Index, Letter, Value&#93; : enumerate(Letters, Vals)) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02422" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2422"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   printf(&quot;Item %zu - %c: %d\\n&quot;, Index, Letter, Value);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02423" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2423"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   Value -= 10;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02424" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2424"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02425" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2425"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// &#96;&#96;&#96;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02426" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2426"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02427" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2427"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Output:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02428" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2428"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   Item 0 - A: 10</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02429" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2429"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   Item 1 - B: 11</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02430" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2430"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   Item 2 - C: 12</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02431" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2431"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   Item 3 - D: 13</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02432" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2432"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02433" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2433"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// or using an iterator:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02434" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2434"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// &#96;&#96;&#96;c++</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02435" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2435"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// for (auto it : enumerate(Vals)) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02436" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2436"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   it.value() += 10;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02437" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2437"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   printf(&quot;Item %zu: %d\\n&quot;, it.index(), it.value());</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02438" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2438"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02439" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2439"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// &#96;&#96;&#96;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02440" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2440"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02441" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2441"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Output:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02442" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2442"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   Item 0: 20</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02443" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2443"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   Item 1: 21</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02444" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2444"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   Item 2: 22</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02446" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2446"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02447" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2447"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">template</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &lt;</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">typename</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> FirstRange, </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">typename</span><span class="doxyHighlight">...
